TopicTitle: Waiter, theres a _____________ in my soup!

Articles.Content:
No no sir, that's hot chocolate! Enjoy your Christmas Season!

Waiter! There's a Santa Hat in my soup!

Sir, that's a bottomless bowl, he fell in and drowned.

 

Waiter! I have a dead mouse in my soup!

Whelp considering you just sipped it, you're probably gonna die...

Waiter! There's a mini-christmas tree in my soup!

Good luck washing THAT down!

 

Waiter! The dead mouse is gone!

Well good!

Waiter! I have no idea how, but you got a baby dolphin in here! Hey little guy! *Gets splashed*

So long and thanks for all your cash

Waiter, there is a towel in my soup.

Sorry; the cook was on dish duty before he started his shift.

Waiter! There's a puppy in my soup!

You DID ask for Kagogi !

 

Waiter, there's broken ceramic in my bowl!

Careful, it is a tad sharp *Badum tss*

Waiter! I need dog-food for my new puppy!

A dog-food is everything your puppy eats, by definition.

Waiter, why this puppy-dog is near the kitchen?

Edited December 15, 2016 by kerbiloid

Another one? I guess the cook is trying to keep them for himself!

Waiter! There's nothing in my soup!

We ran out of puppies.

Waiter! There's a hamster in my soup!

That's impossible! Our soup is 100% beef; not rodent!

Waiter! Someone (@Xorth Tanovar) Is spamming my notifications!

It's as intended, you are in a game after all, and this is a bowl of Competition Chowder.

 

Waiter! there's a @DarkOwl57 in my soup!

*Looks at clone* I don't know what you're talking about.

Waiter! There's a gun in my soup!

Silly boy. That's Pistol Poutine with a side of Rifle Remoulade.

 

Waitress! My absinthe is empty!

It's not a waitress, sir, it's green fairy. Better wake up and go home, it's getting cold under the bench.

Waitress! Another plate of absinthe for that gentleman.

Your plate of absinthe concentrate, sir...

 

Waitress, a round of whatever @kerbiloid is drinking for the entire house! And where's my soup?

I have it. No exceptions

Waiter! There's a really, really, really tall building in my soup!

I'm sorry sir, this is the wrong thread for that
